name":"buildSafeEnv","params":[],"return_type":"Record<string, string>","docstring":"Build a sanitized environment for spawned processes. Only includes non-sensitive variables needed for basic operation.","is_method":false,"is_async":false,"decorators":[],"line_number":782,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"spawnCapture","params":["command: string[]","options?: { timeoutMs?: number; outputCapBytes?: number }"],"return_type":"Promise<SpawnCaptureResult>","docstring":null,"is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":810,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"runInstalledCheck","params":["check: InstalledCheck"],"return_type":"Promise<{ success: boolean; output: string }>","docstring":"Run manifest-defined installed_check command with safety limits. Returns the path/output on success, null on failure. ## Security Properties This function enforces several security constraints: 1. **No shell interpolation**: Commands are passed as arrays to `Bun.spawn()`, preventing shell metacharacter injection (e.g., `; rm -rf /`). 2. **Timeout enforcement**: Commands are killed after `timeoutMs` (default 1.5s) to prevent hangs or resource exhaustion attacks. 3. **Output capping**: Only `outputCapBytes` (default 4KB) are captured to prevent memory exhaustion from malicious output flooding. 4. **Environment sanitization**: Only essential non-sensitive env vars are passed (PATH, HOME, locale settings). API keys and secrets are excluded. 5. **Privilege restriction**: Commands requesting `run_as: root` are skipped. ## Manifest Author Guidelines When writing `installed_check` commands in ACFS manifests: - Use simple, idiomatic checks like `[\"command\", \"-v\", \"toolname\"]` - Avoid shell features (pipes, redirects, subshells) - they won't work - Keep commands fast (< 1.5s by default; or set timeoutMs explicitly) and output minimal (< 4KB) - Don't rely on environment variables beyond PATH/HOME - Test that the command works with minimal privileges","is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":887,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"findExecutable","params":["command: string"],"return_type":"Promise<string | null>","docstring":"Find executable path using 'which' (Unix) or 'where' (Windows). Uses sanitized environment to prevent credential leakage.","is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":959,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"getVersion","params":["commands: string[]","versionFlag: string"],"return_type":"Promise<string | null>","docstring":"Get version from CLI. Uses sanitized environment to prevent credential leakage.","is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":984,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"checkAuth","params":["authCmd: string[]"],"return_type":"Promise<{ authenticated: boolean; error?: string }>","docstring":"Check authentication status. Uses sanitized environment to prevent credential leakage.","is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":1014,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"detectCLI","params":["def: CLIDefinition"],"return_type":"Promise<DetectedCLI>","docstring":"Detect a single CLI using manifest installed_check with fallback to which/where.","is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":1064,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"clearDetectionCache","params":[],"return_type":"void","docstring":null,"is_method":false,"is_async":false,"decorators":[],"line_number":1199,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"detectAgentCLIs","params":[],"return_type":"Promise<DetectedCLI[]>","docstring":null,"is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":1210,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"detectToolCLIs","params":[],"return_type":"Promise<DetectedCLI[]>","docstring":null,"is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_number":1218,"language":"typescript"},{"name":"detectAllCLIs","params":["bypassCache = false"],"return_type":"Promise<DetectionResult>","docstring":null,"is_method":false,"is_async":true,"decorators":[],"line_